&lt;hr&#x2F;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;weapon-swap&quot;&gt;Weapon Swap&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weapon swap is optional&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dagger&#x2F;Dagger&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dagger&#x2F;Torch&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;infusions&quot;&gt;Infusions&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;39337&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Malign Infusion OR&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;39620&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Mighty +5 Agony Infusion&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Optimised Viper&#x27;s Loadout
&lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;gw2skills.net&#x2F;editor&#x2F;?POQAUlZUw+YSMKmJWaXXP3c4hDb3+A-DSJYmRB&#x2F;ZEnCIEJgCPGQTKOrAVA-e&quot;&gt;GW2Skills Link&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;relic&quot;&gt;Relic&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100153&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of the Fractal (standard)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;104424&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of Thorns (situational)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;It is not possible to bench &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;104424&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of Thorns due to the conditions required to trigger it at the golem.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;br&#x2F;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;102199&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of the Blightbringer has been considered but remains a much weaker version as there is a hidden ICD, preventing
Poison Volley from proccing multiple times.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;food&quot;&gt;Food&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;91878&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Cilantro and Cured Meat Flatbread&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;43361&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Koi Cake(budget alternative)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;The difference between using this and standard condition food is minimal.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;br&#x2F;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;utility&quot;&gt;Utility&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;48917&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Toxic Tuning Crystal&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;pets&quot;&gt;Pets&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Janthiri Bee is competitive in damage and provides ready access CC, making it the default best option for raiding.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Wallow provides a poison field, decent healing and condition cleanses which is good in open world.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other options include the Bristleback, Jungle Spider, Jaguar, Warthog and Black Widow.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;build&quot;&gt;Build&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Condi DPS\&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot; class=&quot;language-chatlink z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-chatlink&quot; data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source z-chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-begin&quot;&gt;[&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;DQQeLSE3Ny55AAAAvwAAAOkWAAC6AAAALhYAAEclAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAADawAvAAUAAA==&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-end&quot;&gt;]&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;peticon&quot; style=&quot;background: url(&#x27;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;render.guildwars2.com&#x2F;file&#x2F;DF96C29EFA4BDEC66C3149F280141490C20458D3&#x2F;52606.png&#x27;) 50% 50% no-repeat;&quot;&gt;Juvenile Warthog&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;peticon&quot; style=&quot;background: url(&#x27;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;render.guildwars2.com&#x2F;file&#x2F;03BF0B1C079C06B359E0CE520E747AC5E878F395&#x2F;3594054.png&#x27;) 50% 50% no-repeat;&quot;&gt;Juvenile Janthiri Bee&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;skills&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;31914,12537,40498,12496,45717&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;specializations&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;30,33,55&#x27; data-armory-30-traits=&#x27;1069,1846,1912&#x27; data-armory-33-traits=&#x27;1099,1101,1701&#x27; data-armory-55-traits=&#x27;2071,2161,2128&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;rotation-and-utilities&quot;&gt;Rotation and Utilities&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;dps-rotation&quot;&gt;DPS Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stay merged at all times.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Early Precast - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12476&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Spike Trap and stack dodges.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pre-battle - &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45717&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; One Wolf Pack + &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12537&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sharpening Stone + &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40498&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Vulture Stance + &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45479&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sharpen Spines (if using Bristleback)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Rotation - Use all non-healing skills on cooldown except F1&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;crowd-control&quot;&gt;Crowd Control&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have decent CC by just using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12508&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Concussion Shot (Shortbow 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have many other CC skills littered in your weapon&#x2F;pet&#x2F;utility kit including the ones used to upkeep &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2127&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Twice as Vicious (see below).&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can precast &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12537&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sharpening Stone for additional CC just before the CC phase of an encounter.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;sustainability&quot;&gt;Sustainability&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may opt to take &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12489&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Healing Spring for better condi cleanse&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12517&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Quick Shot (Shortbow 3) is an evade that does a step back. This is useful for bosses with pull mechanics.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you need an extra heal, you may swap your pet to the Wallow for &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;44626&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Spiritual Reprieve&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;optimisation&quot;&gt;Optimisation&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;twice-as-vicious&quot;&gt;Twice as Vicious&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spread out &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12537&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sharpening Stone, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40588&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Primal Cry and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12508&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Concussion Shot to maximise &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2127&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Twice as Vicious uptime.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use your other pet CC skills if your coverage is falling such as &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;75771&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bumble.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;dodging&quot;&gt;Dodging&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Where dodging is necessary, you may delay &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12517&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Quick Shot after the dodge to have better uptime of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1912&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Light on your Feet.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;75771&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bumble can also refresh &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1912&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Light on your Feet.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;benchmark&quot;&gt;Benchmark&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The build is benched with ascended gear and infusions, skipping &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;12517&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Quick Shot (Shortbow 3) to avoid forced movement.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</content>
        
